org.apache.sysds.runtime.compress.colgroup

Class ColGroupValue

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.sysds.runtime.compress.colgroup.AColGroup
      • org.apache.sysds.runtime.compress.colgroup.ColGroupValue
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ColGroupConst, ColGroupDDC, ColGroupEmpty, ColGroupOffset, ColGroupSDC, ColGroupSDCSingle, ColGroupSDCSingleZeros, ColGroupSDCZeros

    public abstract class ColGroupValue
extends AColGroup
implements Cloneable
    Base class for column groups encoded with value dictionary. This include column groups such as DDC OLE and RLE.

      • getCounts

        public final int[] getCounts()
        Returns the counts of values inside the dictionary. If already calculated it will return the previous counts. This produce an overhead in cases where the count is calculated, but the overhead will be limited to number of distinct tuples in the dictionary. The returned counts always contains the number of zeros as well if there are some contained, even if they are not materialized.
        Returns:
        the count of each value in the MatrixBlock.

      • getCounts

        public final int[] getCounts(int rl,
                             int ru)
        Returns the counts of values inside the MatrixBlock returned in getValuesAsBlock Throws an exception if the getIfCountsType is false. The returned counts always contains the number of zeros as well if there are some contained, even if they are not materialized.
        Parameters:
        rl - the lower index of the interval of rows queried
        ru - the the upper boundary of the interval of rows queried
        Returns:
        the count of each value in the MatrixBlock.

        public AColGroup sliceColumns(int cl,
                              int cu)
        Description copied from class: AColGroup
        Slice out the columns within the range of cl and cu to remove the dictionary values related to these columns. If the ColGroup slicing from does not contain any columns within the range null is returned.
        Specified by:
        sliceColumns in class AColGroup
        Parameters:
        cl - The lower bound of the columns to select
        cu - The upper bound of the columns to select (not inclusive).
        Returns:
        A cloned Column Group, with a copied pointer to the old column groups index structure, but reduced dictionary and _columnIndexes correctly aligned with the expected sliced compressed matrix.
